parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belts can lead to serious injuries or fatalities in the event of an accident, as the occupant may not be properly restrained.
symptoms: The seat belts do not retract
the seat belt buckles fail to release
the seat belt buckles fail to latch
the seat belt housing falls off.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure to honor the recall can lead to the continued use of defective seat belts, which can cause serious injuries or fatalities in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The dealership or manufacturer refuses to repair or replace the defective seat belts
and the parts are no longer available.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Frame Crack/Failure due to Design and/or Missing Reinforcement
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The cracking or failure of the frame can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities. It can also result in costly repairs and downtime.
symptoms: The vehicle's frame cracks or breaks
or drift into other lanes. The frame may flex against the steering gear box

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cooling system can cause engine overheating, leading to engine damage, failure, or even fires, which can result in accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
The failure of the engine block can cause engine failure, leading to loss of power, stalling, or even accidents, which can result in injuries or fatalities.
The failure of the oil pan gasket can cause oil leaks, leading to engine damage, failure, or even fires, which can result in accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
The failure of the catalytic converter can cause decreased engine performance, decreased fuel efficiency, and increased emissions, which can lead to environmental harm and decreased air quality.
Engine compartment fires can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities, as well as damage to the vehicle and surrounding property.
symptoms: smoke or flames from the engine compartment.
